## PCAP-to-Flow Feature Extraction

This folder also contains scripts used to convert raw packet captures into tabular datasets for machine learning experiments.

| File | Scenario | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `PCAP to FLOW-DO53.py` | Do53 | Extracts features from conventional DNS traffic over port 53 and generates `dataset_Do53.csv` and `stats_Do53.csv`. |
| `PCAP to FLOW-DOH.py` | DoH | Extracts flow-based features from DNS-over-HTTPS traffic over TCP/443 and generates `dataset_DoH.csv`, `doh_clienthello_report.csv` and `stats_DoH.csv`. |

### Do53 Feature Extraction

The Do53 script processes `.pcap` and `.pcapng` files containing conventional DNS traffic. It extracts lexical, structural and DNS-related attributes from queries and responses.

The generated dataset contains 29 features plus the target label.

Main extracted feature groups include:

- query length and subdomain length
- number of labels
- maximum and average label length
- entropy
- digit, uppercase, lowercase and special character ratios
- DNS record type and query class
- TTL-related attributes
- Base64 and hexadecimal pattern indicators
- dictionary-word indicator
- vowel and consonant ratios
- number of distinct characters
- domain-level aggregate statistics
- failed-query ratio

The expected output files are:

```text
dataset_Do53.csv
stats_Do53.csv
